### What problem does this feature solve?

If use `<Select />` with remote loaded options, we need to customize all option items in select list. For now, each option only contains a label text. But if we need more information to be show in each item, it is not possible.

![](https://github.com/ant-design/ant-design/assets/525658/16c0a5be-c235-4ff6-aded-dc607a855f61)

Or we can not just use `options` property, but change to use `data.map(item => <Option>)` style.

### What does the proposed API look like?

```
function SomeFunctionComponet({ option, index, options }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <span>{index + 1}.</span>
      <span>{option.label}</span>
      <span>{option.data.date}</span>
    </div>
  );
}

function MySelect() {
  return (
    <Select
      optionRender={SomeFunctionComponet}
    />
  );
}
```

