### Steps to reproduce
use react `useRef` hook, and pass it to the `<Image />` Component.

### What is expected?
The ref to contain a reference to the underling `<img />`

### What is actually happening?
The ref is being used for something else in `rc-image`.
#### From [`rc-image`](https://github.com/react-component/image/blob/8bddb472d0818725ccb9038842bfaa6bb96736f4/src/Image.tsx#L161)
```
<img
    {...imgCommonProps}
     ref={getImgRef}
     ... 
/>
``` 
#### `getImgRef` :
```
const getImgRef = (img?: HTMLImageElement) => {
    isLoaded.current = false;
    if (status !== 'loading') return;
    if (img?.complete && (img.naturalWidth || img.naturalHeight)) {
      isLoaded.current = true;
      onLoad();
    }
  };
```

